HEADWORD: Mallet
<hw>Mal"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>maillet</ets>, dim. of <ets>mail</ets>. See <er>Mall</er> a
beetle.]</ety> <def>A small maul with a short handle, -- used esp. for
driving a tool, as a chisel or the like; also, a light beetle with a
long handle, -- used in playing croquet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malleus</ent>⟦br⟧
